==Etymology==
:from the Greek ''dialektos'', meaning ''conversation''.

===Noun===
#a variety of a [[language]] (often a spoken variety, specifically) that is characteristic of a particular area, community or group. Dialects of a language represent relatively minor differences in vocabulary, as well as differences in style, spelling and pronunciation.
#: '' A language is a dialect with an army and a navy''
#:Note: The difference between a language and a dialect is not always clear, but it is generally considered that people of different dialects can understand each other, while people of different languages cannot. (''cf.'' [[species]] in the biological sense)

